📘 Spring Boot Starters — Complete Guide (For Beginners & Professionals)
⭐ What Are Spring Boot Starters?
Spring Boot starters are pre‑packaged dependency bundles that bring all the required libraries for a specific feature.

Instead of manually adding 10–20 dependencies, you add one starter, and Spring Boot pulls everything you need.

Think of starters as combo meals — one item gives you everything.

⭐ Why Starters Exist
Starters solve three major problems:

Simplify dependency management

Avoid version conflicts

Provide ready‑to‑use configurations

Reduce boilerplate

Help you start coding immediately

